{"title":"Northern Ireland fact of the day","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/905797784/0/marginalrevolution~Northern-Ireland-fact-of-the-day.html","date":1728300945000,"content":"<blockquote><p>The NHS in Northern Ireland is the worst in the UK.  During the quarter April/June 2021, over 349,000 people were waiting for a first appointment, 53 percent for over a year, an increase of 39,000 for the same period in 2020.  Adjusted for population size, waiting lists in Northern Ireland are 100 times greater than those in England, a country 50 times its size.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>That is from the truly excellent <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Perils-Prospects-Ireland-Padraig-OMalley/dp/1843518511/ref=sr_1_1?crid=CEP5R4T9PABF&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.LC-2LG4cXFFM0LIrIQum2Q.X5Goz2Ak23BpszO5Mhbt9YTetmzW8mr994l2wziZL6o&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Perils+and+Prospects+of+a+United+Ireland&amp;qid=1728300878&amp;sprefix=perils+and+prospects+of+a+united+ireland%2Caps%2C124&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Perils and Prospects of a United Ireland</a>, by Padraig O’Malley.  Imagine a detailed, thoughtful 500 pp. book on political issues you probably don’t care all that much about — is there any better way to study politics and political reasoning?  Every page of this book offers substance.</p>\r\n<p>Elsewhere, of course, we are told that reluctance to give up their health care system is a major reason why Irish reunification is not more popular in the North, and that holds for Catholics too.</p>\r\n<p>This one will make the best non-fiction of the year list.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/10/northern-ireland-fact-of-the-day.html\">Northern Ireland fact of the day</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img